#MEM id=saas-metrics source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/skills/marketplace/saas-metrics/SKILL.md
M|saas-metrics|name: avinyc:business
M|saas-metrics|description: SaaS unit economics and growth str. Use for LTV, CAC, MRR/ARR analysis, payback period, churn analysis, Rule of 40, and SaaS financial modeling. Triggers on "unit economics", "ltv", "cac"
M|saas-metrics|argument-hint: "[metric or question]"
M|saas-metrics|user-invocable: true
M|saas-metrics|Growth and metrics expert specializing in SaaS businesses, performance mkt, conversion optimization, and unit economics.
M|saas-metrics|**This skill covers:** Strategic metrics, unit economics, investor-ready analysis, and business health assessment. Use for questions like "Is my business healthy?", "What's my LTV:CAC?", or "Am I read
M|saas-metrics|**Use the mkt skill instead for:** Funnel mechanics, cg optimization, ad spend allocation, and acquisition tactics.
M|saas-metrics|- **CPM (Cost Per Mille)**: Calculate effective CPM across channels (Facebook, Google, LinkedIn, Twitter). Understand platform-specific benchmarks by industry.
M|saas-metrics|- **CPC (Cost Per Click)**: Optimize click costs through ad creative testing, audience refinement, and bid str.
M|saas-metrics|- **CTR (Click-Through Rate)**: Improve CTR through creative iteration, copy testing, and audience-message fit.
M|saas-metrics|- **CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost)**: Calculate blended and channel-specific CAC, including all touch points.
M|saas-metrics|- **Conversion Rate Optimization (CRO)**: Design and analyze A/B tests for headlines, value props, soc proof, and CTAs.
M|saas-metrics|- **Micro-conversions**: Track email captures, cnt downloads, demo requests, waitlist signups.
M|saas-metrics|- **Attribution modeling**: Implement multi-touch attribution to understand true channel value.
M|saas-metrics|- **Landing page metrics**: Time on page, bounce rate, scroll depth, heat mapping analysis.
M|saas-metrics|- **Waitlist CAC**: Calculate cost to acquire each waitlist signup across channels.
M|saas-metrics|- **Waitlist-to-Customer Conversion**: Model expected conversion rates based on engagement signals.
M|saas-metrics|- **Decay rates**: Understand and model waitlist interest decay over time.
M|saas-metrics|- **Activation strategies**: Design cg to maintain waitlist engagement and improve launch conversion.
M|saas-metrics|- **MRR/ARR**: Track new, expansion, churned, and reactivation MRR. Calculate ARR with proper treatment of annual contracts.
M|saas-metrics|- **LTV (Lifetime Value)**: Calculate using cohort-based retention curves, not simple averages.
M|saas-metrics|- **LTV:CAC Ratio**: Understand healthy ratios by business model (self-serve vs sales-assisted).
M|saas-metrics|- **Payback Period**: Calculate months to recover CAC by customer segment.
M|saas-metrics|- **Net Dollar Retention**: Track expansion revenue versus churn by cohort.
M|saas-metrics|- **Rule of 40**: Balance growth rate and profitability for valuation optimization.
M|saas-metrics|1. **Start with the funnel**: Map entire customer journey from first touch to revenue
M|saas-metrics|2. **Identify bottlenecks**: Find biggest opportunities using data
M|saas-metrics|3. **Calculate scenarios**: Model best, expected, and worst-case outcomes
M|saas-metrics|4. **Benchmark intelligently**: Compare to relevant peer sets, not generic averages
M|saas-metrics|5. **Focus on actionable insights**: Every analysis ends with specific, testable recommendations
M|saas-metrics|- Blended CAC hiding unprofitable channels
M|saas-metrics|- Vanity metrics replacing actionable ones
M|saas-metrics|- Ignoring cohort effects in retention analysis
M|saas-metrics|- Overestimating waitlist conversion rates
M|saas-metrics|- Underestimating time to product-market fit
M|saas-metrics|- Not accounting for seasonality in projections
M|saas-metrics|anl: Mixpanel, Amplitude, Segment, Google anl, Heap
M|saas-metrics|Ads: Facebook Ads Manager, Google Ads, LinkedIn cg Manager
M|saas-metrics|CRO: Optimizely, VWO, Google Optimize
M|saas-metrics|Subscription metrics: Baremetrics, ProfitWell, ChartMogul